I became a fan of the Peppas franchise when a friend put me on to the chicken from the Utica location. I was excited about the franchise opening a restaurant closer to home but the food at this location is below average.  Opening week the chicken was bomb: flavorful, seasoned and cooked properly. After the first two weeks, things started going downhill (chicken not cooked properly/still pink or if you order via uberEATs not receiving the sauce even when you pay for extra.)  There was a moment when things started to improve but then it went downhill again and because of that I will no longer eat from this location. I have ordered in-store and via uberEATs and my experience in-store were a lot better (last-time I was in-store was in September). I personally didn't mind the long wait in-store when the chicken was good. My most recent orders were through UberEats and each time it was something: sauce or part of order missing, festival not fried properly, burnt chicken.  I really hope this restaurant gets it together because I would like to see it succeed since it is black-owned business. Please listen to your customers and get rid of the person(s) currently cooking the chicken.

I rated it 4 stars because the food is way too spicy . I got Rasta pasta with stew chicken. I bought a large with the intentions to share with my son but it was way too spicy for him. I am Caribbean so I understand we cook with spices, however when cooking for a large crowd you have to be aware that everyone does not like spicy food . I’m personally not a spicy food fan so I had to keep drinking water after every bite . Consider giving ppl the option to add pepper to their individual platters rather than making the big batch so spicy. Despite I will return and try a different option. Thanks
